text:
Bouck Ave., east side, between Boston Road and Givan Ave. The view is southward.

October 1927.

New York World.

Bouck Ave., east side, south from but not including Boston Road, to but not including Givan Ave.

About 1929.

General Photographic Company.

(1) A lone squatters shack, atop a group of boulders, at the S.E. corner of Holland Ave., and 213th Street, Bronx, N.Y.

November 11, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) Another squatter, at East 213th Street, and the N.W. corner of Boston Road, in the Bronx.

November 11, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

(3) Another squatters shack, at the intersection of Boston Road and East 213th Street, (on the Boston Road side).

November 11, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Squatters Colony - Bronx.
